third-party components vendored under lib/

glad -- the opengl loader in lib/gl.h was generated by glad 2.0.8
(https://gen.glad.sh/) for the gl 3.3 core profile, header-only with the loader included.
regenerate with the same options at:
https://gen.glad.sh/#generator=c&api=gl%3D3.3&profile=gl%3Dcore&options=HEADER_ONLY%2CLOADER
the glad generator is MIT-licensed (https://github.com/Dav1dde/glad); its generated output
carries no separate obligations. the header inlines Khronos khrplatform.h.

rgfw -- lib/RGFW.h is a single-header window + opengl context library by Riley Mabb
(@ColleagueRiley), v2.0.0-dev, from https://github.com/ColleagueRiley/RGFW. zlib/libpng
licensed. carries one local change (keyable macos fullscreen, tagged "pixel-goo local
patch" inline) -- see lib/patches/rgfw-fullscreen-keyable.patch for the diff against
pristine upstream and the re-apply procedure.

cglm -- lib/cglm/ is a header-only C math library by Recep Aslantas (@recp), v0.9.6, from
https://github.com/recp/cglm. MIT licensed -- see LICENSE-cglm.

nob -- lib/nob.h is a single-header C build system by Alexey Kutepov (@rexim / tsoding),
v3.8.2, from https://github.com/tsoding/nob.h. dual-licensed MIT / public domain (the
Unlicense); used here under the public domain option.

dropt -- lib/dropt/ is a small command-line option parser by James D. Lin (@jamesderlin),
v2.0.0, from https://github.com/jamesderlin/dropt. zlib-licensed.
